        Parameters:

        installedAppId - The ID of the installed application. (required)
        locationId - The ID of the location that both the installed smart app and source are associated with. (optional)

      • deleteInstallation

        DeleteInstalledAppResponse deleteInstallation(java.lang.String authorization,
                                              java.lang.String installedAppId,
                                              java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> queryParams)
        Delete an installed app. Delete an Installed App. Note, this is equivalent to the other deleteInstallation method, but with the query parameters collected into a single Map parameter. This is convenient for services with optional query parameters, especially when used with the InstalledappsApi.DeleteInstallationQueryParams class that allows for building up this map in a fluent style.
        Parameters:
        authorization - OAuth token (required)
        installedAppId - The ID of the installed application. (required)
        queryParams - Map of query parameters as name-value pairs

        The following elements may be specified in the query map:

        • locationId - The ID of the location that both the installed smart app and source are associated with. (optional)
        Returns:
        DeleteInstalledAppResponse
